source.name: Youth Indicators 2011 America's Youth: Transitions to Adulthood
source.description: This annual report provides a compilation of over 50 downloadable tables of statistical information covering demographics, school-related characteristics, employment-related characteristics, activities outside of school and work, health and wellness and future goals related to the lives of youth.  This report examines numerous aspects of the lives of youth and young adults, ages 14 to 24, in the United States over the last several decades. The report features status and trend data from multiple surveys on the distribution of youth and their family structure; on school-, employment-, and health-related factors; and on future plans.
